This paper involves machine learning techniques to automate algorithm design, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Specifically, the paper uses reinforcement learning (RL) to learn an optimization algorithm, which is a subfield of RL and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which can be categorized under the subfields of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves software engineering aspects, such as the implementation and evaluation of the learned algorithm, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
